ğŸ”¹ Necessary Conditions for Isomorphism (PYQ FAVORITE)

If two graphs are isomorphic, they must have:

Same number of vertices

Same number of edges

Same degree sequence

Same number of connected components

Same number of cycles of each length

ğŸ“Œ Important:
These are necessary but NOT sufficient.

ğŸ”¹ Degree Sequence Check (Very Common)

Sort vertex degrees in non-decreasing order.

If degree sequences differ â†’ NOT isomorphic.

If same â†’ further checking required.

ğŸ”¹ Quick GATE Tricks

âœ” Check:

Degree pattern

Number of triangles

Number of pendant vertices

Adjacency relationships

ğŸ“Œ GATE Trap:
Same degree sequence â‰  automatically isomorphic.

